news.title: CIFI Holdings' suspended debt repayments add to China's property woes
news.para: CIFI said in a filing it has engaged Haitong International Securities Company Limited as financial advisor and Linklaters as legal adviser to facilitate a restructuring of its $6.85 billion offshore debt, as it is likely to come under continued pressure to generate sufficient cash for repayments.

news.title: China: Greenland Holdings seeks offshore bond payment extension
news.para: State-backed Greenland joins a string of Chinese developers that have delayed or defaulted on offshore debt obligations since the second half of last year due to a stifling cash squeeze triggered partly by a regulatory crackdown.

news.title: Dehradun civic body to charge user fees for multi-storeyed apartments
news.para: User fees have been increased up to five times as a shopkeeper has to pay Rs 100 per month for running a shop in residential areas, instead of present Rs 20.

news.title: Gurugram: Finally, new power connections for flats at Vipul World
news.para: DHBVN has finally started releasing new electricity connections to Vipul World, a housing society on Sohna road in Sector 48, with the developer handing over the required bank guarantee of Rs 10 crore and land to the power discom for the construction of a 33 KV substation.

news.title: Land reserved for house sites to poor in Amaravati master plan
news.para: The CRDA board has already authorised the changes in the master plan and also the proposal to allocate house sites to the poor. The amendments to CRDA Act have also got the approval of governor Biswabhusan Harichandan.

news.title: Chandigarh: CHB gives chance to allottees whose flats were found locked during survey
news.para: In the survey, 1,268 (7%) out of 18,138 allotted houses under rehabilitation scheme, small flat scheme and affordable rental housing scheme were found to be locked.

news.title: Housing scheme likely to bring financial liability for Thiruvananthapuram corporation
news.para: The Smart City Thiruvananthapuram Ltd (SCTL) board has put the burden of price escalation of the project on the corporation citing the civic body’s failure in handing over the project site to the contractor on time.

news.title: Rajasthan: High bajri prices rattle construction industry and ordinary people alike
news.para: On Sunday, the mining department announced that bajri excavation from a total 28 leases have now been allowed in the state and that 90% of the demand of the bajri would now be fulfilled.

news.title: Gurugram civic body fines 22 for violating GRAP norms in a day
news.para: One challan amounting to Rs 1 lakh was issued on Monday for violating the construction ban. The maximum number of 12 challans amounting to Rs 1.05 lakh were issued for keeping uncovered construction material.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Closed textile units look to unlock land value
news.para: Sources say all these closed units were set up decades ago and their land value has increased manyfold, so many are evaluating the option of unlocking their land value and shifting units away from the city.

news.title: Structural stability certification rule remains on paper in Ahmedabad
news.para: Unfortunately, the Ahmedabad Urban Development Authority (AUDA), the implementing authority, doesn't have the time or will to implement this rule.

news.title: Deputy registrar's office will be set up in Noida soon
news.para: This was announced by Varun Khare, deputy registrar of societies, at a meeting with members of the Noida Federation of Apartment Owners Associations (NOFAA) in Meerut.

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai city falls 3% to 8,276 units in October 2022
news.para: Real estate consultant Knight Frank India said that Mumbai city (BMC area) saw property sale registrations of 8,276 units in October 2022, contributing over Rs 705 crore to the state revenues.

news.title: Panel to look into issues of realtors in Navi Mumbai
news.para: As per the urban development department’s order, developers and builders in Navi Mumbai are facing issues, after Cidco leased out lands.

news.title: Punjab National Bank & Bank of India hike lending rates
news.para: The MCLR with effect from November 1, 2022 shall be revised with the benchmark one-year tenor rate at 8.05 per cent as against the 7.75 per cent existing rate, PNB said in a regulatory filing.
